    Author:
    csc207 student This class defines a JugPuzzle composed by a certain number of Jug instances. This class is used by the JugPuzzleController class.

      • move

        public void move(int from,
                 int to)
        Initiates a move in the JugPuzzle by transfering an amount of units of liquid from a specified Jug instance to another specified Jug instance, while increasing the number of moves made in the puzzle.
        Parameters:
        from - Number ID of the Jug that transfer a certain amount of units of liquid.
        to - Number ID of the Jug that is filled by a certain amount of units of liquid.

      • isPuzzleSolved

        public boolean isPuzzleSolved()
        Returns:
        Returns true if the JugPuzzle is solved. Returns false if otherwise.

      • spill

        public void spill(Jug fromJug,
                  Jug toJug)
        A certain amount of units of liquid is removed from a specified Jug and transferred to another specified Jug. The amount of liquid transferred from the specified Jug depends on its current amount and the amount required to fill up the specified Jug.
        Parameters:
        fromJug - Jug to which a certain amount of units of liquid is removed.
        toJug - Jug to which a certain amount of units of liquid will be added.
